-> Change Path Variables at the top of the Cronjob Scripts if needed
-> Change Config.php Settings
-> Change the Postfix Configuration to use Relaydomains
(see postfix-main.cf)

Cronjob cronjob-autobind -> If you use a bind slave server this script
will copy the domains from bind to your bxccs backup site (this script and postfix)
Cronjob cronjob -> This script is to create the postfix configuration out of the
database entries made by the autodns cronjob or you manually

Default Login is
Username: admin
Passwort: adminLogMeIn

CONFIGURATE POSTFIX (NEEDED URGENTLY TO RUN THIS MODULE) CRONJOB.PHP
-----------------------------------------------------------------
unlink PATHTOBINDFILEINCRONJOBFOLDER; 
cp /etc/bind/named.conf.local PATHTOCRONJOBFOLDERBINDFILE;
chown www-data PATHTOCRONJOBFOLDERBINDFILE;
chgrp www-data PATHTOCRONJOBFOLDERBINDFILE; 
php PATHTOCRONJOBFOLDER/cronjob-autobind.php;

My Cron Looks like this:
chown www-data /var/www/html/* -R; chgrp www-data /var/www/html/* -R;php7.4 /var/www/html/bxccs/cronjob/cronjob.php; unlink /etc/postfix/transportmaps; unlink /etc/postfix/relaydomains;mv /var/www/html/bxccs/cronjob/transportmaps /etc/postfix/transportmaps; mv /var/www/html/bxccs/cronjob/relaydomains /etc/postfix/relaydomains;/usr/sbin/postmap /etc/postfix/relaydomains; /usr/sbin/postmap /etc/postfix/transportmaps; /etc/init.d/postfix reload


AUTODNS CRONJOB EXAMPLE 
---------------------------------------------
php PATHTOCRONJOB.PHP; 
unlink /etc/postfix/transportmaps; 
unlink /etc/postfix/relaydomains;
mv PATHTOCRONJOBFOLDER/transportmaps /etc/postfix/transportmaps; 
mv PATHTOCRONJOBFOLDER/relaydomains /etc/postfix/relaydomains;
/usr/sbin/postmap /etc/postfix/relaydomains;
/usr/sbin/postmap /etc/postfix/transportmaps;
/etc/init.d/postfix reload

unlink /var/www/html/bxccs/cronjob/bindfile.bind; cp /etc/bind/named.conf.local /var/www/html/bxccs/cronjob/bindfile.bind;chown www-data /var/www/html/bxccs/cronjob/bindfile.bind; chgrp www-data /var/www/html/bxccs/cronjob/bindfile.bind; php /var/www/html/bxccs/cronjob/cronjob-autobind.php;


CONFIG FOR POSTFIX main.cf
-------------------------------------

smtpd_banner = $myhostname ESMTP $mail_name (Debian/GNU)
biff = no

append_dot_mydomain = no
readme_directory = no
compatibility_level = 2

smtpd_tls_cert_file=PATHTOSSLCERT
smtpd_tls_key_file=PATHTOSSLCERTKEY
smtpd_use_tls=yes
smtpd_tls_session_cache_database = btree:${data_directory}/smtpd_scache
smtp_tls_session_cache_database = btree:${data_directory}/smtp_scache


smtpd_relay_restrictions = permit_mynetworks permit_sasl_authenticated reject_unauth_destination
myhostname = SERVERHOSTNAME
alias_maps = hash:/etc/aliases
alias_database = hash:/etc/aliases
myorigin = /etc/mailname
mydestination = $myhostname, localhost
relayhost =
mynetworks = 127.0.0.0/8 [::ffff:127.0.0.0]/104 [::1]/128
mailbox_size_limit = 0
recipient_delimiter = +
inet_interfaces = all
inet_protocols = all
maximal_queue_lifetime = 30d

relay_recipient_maps =
relay_domains = hash:/etc/postfix/relaydomains
transport_maps = hash:/etc/postfix/transportmaps
